jnxOspfv3MIB.name: jnxOspfv3MIB

revisions.description: Initial version, published as RFC xxxx
Deprecating all objects. New mib file rfc5643.mib takes care of these objects.

JnxOspfv3UpToRefreshIntervalTc.name: JnxOspfv3UpToRefreshIntervalTc
JnxOspfv3UpToRefreshIntervalTc.description: The values one might be able to configure for variables bounded by the Refresh Interval

JnxOspfv3DeadIntRangeTc.name: JnxOspfv3DeadIntRangeTc
JnxOspfv3DeadIntRangeTc.description: The range, in seconds, of dead interval value.

JnxOspfv3RouterIdTc.name: JnxOspfv3RouterIdTc
JnxOspfv3RouterIdTc.description: A 32-bit, unsigned integer uniquely identifying the router in the Autonomous System. To ensure uniqueness, this may default to the value of one of the router's IPv4 host addresses if IPv4 is configured on the router.

jnxOspfv3RouterId.name: jnxOspfv3RouterId
jnxOspfv3RouterId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the router in the Autonomous System. To ensure uniqueness, this may default to the value of one of the router's IPv4 host addresses, represented as a 32-bit unsigned integer, if IPv4 is configured on the router.

jnxOspfv3AdminStat.name: jnxOspfv3AdminStat
jnxOspfv3AdminStat.description: The administrative status of OSPFv3 in the router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the OSPFv3 Process is active on at least one interface; 'disabled' disables it on all interfaces.

jnxOspfv3VersionNumber.name: jnxOspfv3VersionNumber
jnxOspfv3VersionNumber.description: The version number of OSPF for IPv6 is 3.

jnxOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.name: jnxOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus
jnxOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 3 Splitting the AS into Areas
jnxOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.description: A flag to note whether this router is an area border router.

jnxOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus.name: jnxOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus
jnxOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 3.3 Classification of routers
jnxOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus.description: A flag to note whether this router is configured as an Autonomous System border router.

jnxOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount.name: jnxOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount
jnxOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount.description: The number of AS-Scope (e.g. AS-External) link state advertisements in the link state database.

jnxOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum.name: jnxOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum
jnxOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the LS checksums of the AS-scoped link state advertisements contained in the link state database. This sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link state database of two routers.

jnxOspfv3OriginateNewLsas.name: jnxOspfv3OriginateNewLsas
jnxOspfv3OriginateNewLsas.description: The number of new link-state advertisements that have been originated. This number is incremented each time the router originates a new LSA.

jnxOspfv3RxNewLsas.name: jnxOspfv3RxNewLsas
jnxOspfv3RxNewLsas.description: The number of link state advertisements received determined to be new instantiations. This number does not include newer instantiations of self-originated link state advertisements.

jnxOspfv3ExtLsaCount.name: jnxOspfv3ExtLsaCount
jnxOspfv3ExtLsaCount.description: The number of External(LS type 0x4005) in the link state database

jnxOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.name: jnxOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit
jnxOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.description: The maximum number of non-default AS-external-LSAs entries that can be stored in the link state database. If the value is -1, then there is no limit. When the number of non-default AS-external-LSAs in a router's link-state database reaches ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit, the router enters Overflow state. The router never holds more than ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit non-default AS-external-LSAs in its database. Ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit MUST be set identically in all routers attached to the OSPFv3 backbone and/or any regular OSPFv3 area. (i.e., OSPFv3 stub areas and NSSAs are excluded).

jnxOspfv3MulticastExtensions.name: jnxOspfv3MulticastExtensions
jnxOspfv3MulticastExtensions.description: A Bit Mask indicating whether the router is forwarding IPv6 multicast datagrams based on the algorithms defined in the Multicast Extensions to OSPF. If intraAreaMulticast set, indicates that the router can forward IPv6 multicast datagrams in the router's directly attached areas (called intra-area multicast routing). If interAreaMulticast set, indicates that the router can forward IPv6 multicast datagrams between OSPFv3 areas (called inter-area multicast routing). If interAsMulticast set, indicates that the router can forward IPv6 multicast datagrams between Autonomous Systems (called inter-AS multicast routing). Only certain combinations of bit settings are allowed, namely: - All bits cleared (no multicasting) - intraAreaMulticast only, - intraAreaMulticast and interAreaMulticast, - intraAreaMulticast and interAsMulticast - intraAreaMulticast, interAreaMulticast and interAsMulticast By default, all bits are cleared.

jnxOspfv3ExitOverflowInterval.name: jnxOspfv3ExitOverflowInterval
jnxOspfv3ExitOverflowInterval.description: The number of seconds that, after entering Overflow State, a router will attempt to leave Overflow State. This allows the router to again originate non-default, AS-External-LSAs. When set to 0, the router will not leave Overflow State until restarted.

jnxOspfv3DemandExtensions.name: jnxOspfv3DemandExtensions
jnxOspfv3DemandExtensions.reference: Ospf Version 2, Appendix on Demand Routing
jnxOspfv3DemandExtensions.description: The router's support for demand routing.

jnxOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth.name: jnxOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth
jnxOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth.description: Reference bandwidth in kilobits/second for calculating default interface metrics. The default value is 100,000 KBPS (100 MBPS)

jnxOspfv3RestartSupport.name: jnxOspfv3RestartSupport
jnxOspfv3RestartSupport.description: The router's support for OSPF Graceful restart. Options include: no restart support, only planned restarts or both planned and unplanned restarts.

jnxOspfv3RestartInterval.name: jnxOspfv3RestartInterval
jnxOspfv3RestartInterval.description: Configured OSPF Graceful restart timeout interval.

jnxOspfv3RestartStatus.name: jnxOspfv3RestartStatus
jnxOspfv3RestartStatus.description: The current status of OSPF Graceful restart capability.

jnxOspfv3RestartAge.name: jnxOspfv3RestartAge
jnxOspfv3RestartAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF Graceful restart interval.

jnxOspfv3RestartExitRc.name: jnxOspfv3RestartExitRc
jnxOspfv3RestartExitRc.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at a Graceful restart. none:............no restart has yet been attempted. inProgress:......a restart attempt is currently underway. completed:.......the last restart completed successfully. timedOut:........the last restart timed out. topologyChanged:.the last restart was aborted due to a topology change.

jnxOspfv3NotificationEnable.name: jnxOspfv3NotificationEnable
jnxOspfv3NotificationEnable.description: If this object is set to true(1), then it enables the generation of OSPFv3 Notifications. If it is set to false(2), these notifications are not generated. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.

jnxOspfv3AreaTable.name: jnxOspfv3AreaTable
jnxOspfv3AreaTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 6 The Area Data Structure
jnxOspfv3AreaTable.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of the router's attached areas. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as a part of RFC 5643.

jnxOspfv3AreaEntry.name: jnxOspfv3AreaEntry
jnxOspfv3AreaEntry.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of one of the router's attached areas.

jnxOspfv3AreaId.name: jnxOspfv3AreaId
jnxOspfv3AreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
jnxOspfv3AreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an area. Area ID 0 is used for the OSPFv3 backbone.

jnxOspfv3ImportAsExtern.name: jnxOspfv3ImportAsExtern
jnxOspfv3ImportAsExtern.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
jnxOspfv3ImportAsExtern.description: Indicates whether an area is a Stub area, NSSA, or standard area. AS-scope LSAs are not imported into Stub Areas or NSSAs. NSSAs import AS-External data as NSSA LSAs which have Area-scope

jnxOspfv3AreaSpfRuns.name: jnxOspfv3AreaSpfRuns
jnxOspfv3AreaSpfRuns.description: The number of times that the intra-area route table has been calculated using this area's link state database. This is typically done using Dijkstra's algorithm.

jnxOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount.name: jnxOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount
jnxOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount.description: The total number of area border routers reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each SPF Pass.

jnxOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount
jnxOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount.description: The total number of Autonomous System border routers reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each SPF Pass.

jnxOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount.name: jnxOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount
jnxOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Area-Scope link state advertisements in this area's link state database.

jnxOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum.name: jnxOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum
jnxOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Area-Scope link state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this area's link state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link-state database of two routers.

jnxOspfv3AreaSummary.name: jnxOspfv3AreaSummary
jnxOspfv3AreaSummary.description: The variable ospfv3AreaSummary controls the import of Inter-Area LSAs into stub and NSSA areas. It has no effect on other areas. If it is noAreaSummary, the router will neither originate nor propagate Inter-Area LSAs into the stub or NSSA area. It will rely entirely on its default route. If it is sendAreaSummary, the router will both summarize and propagate Inter-Area LSAs.

jnxOspfv3AreaStatus.name: jnxOspfv3AreaStatus
jnxOspfv3AreaStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

jnxOspfv3StubMetric.name: jnxOspfv3StubMetric
jnxOspfv3StubMetric.description: The metric value advertised for the default route into Stub and NSSA areas.

jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole.name: jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole
jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole.description: Indicates an NSSA Border router's ability to perform NSSA translation of NSSA-LSAs into AS-External-LSAs.

jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState.name: jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState
jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState.description: Indicates if and how an NSSA Border router is performing NSSA translation of NSSA-LSAs into AS-External-LSA's. When this object is set to enabled, the NSSA Border router's ospfv3AreaNssTranslatorRole has been set to always. When this object is set to elected, a candidate NSSA Border router is translating NSSA-LSA's into AS-External-LSA's. When this object is set to disabled, a candidate NSSA Border router is NOT translating NSSA-LSA's into AS-External-LSA's.

jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabInt.name: jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabInt
jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabInt.description: The number of seconds after an elected translator determines its services are no longer required, that it should continue to perform its translation duties.

jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents.name: jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents
jnxOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents.description: Indicates the number of Translator State changes that have occurred since the last boot-up.

jnxOspfv3AreaStubMetricType.name: jnxOspfv3AreaStubMetricType
jnxOspfv3AreaStubMetricType.description: This variable displays the type of metric advertised as a default route.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbTable.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbTable
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's AS-Scope Link State Database. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as a part of RFC 5643.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbEntry.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbEntry
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbEntry.description: A single AS-Scope Link State Advertisement.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbType.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbType
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format. AS-Scope LSAs not recognized by the router may be stored in the database.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbLsid.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbLsid
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbSequence
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbAge.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbAge
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown.description: Indicates whether the LSA type is recognized by this Router.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbTable.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbTable
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's Area-Scope Link State Database. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as a part of RFC 5643.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry.description: A single Area-Scope Link State Advertisement.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.description: The 32-bit identifier of the Area from which the LSA was received.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbType.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbType
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format. Area-Scope LSAs unrecognized by the router are also stored in this database.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbLsid.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbLsid
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbAge.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbAge
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown.description: Indicates whether the LSA type is recognized by this Router.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbTable.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbTable
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's Link-Scope Link State Database. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as a part of RFC 5643.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry.description: A single Link-Scope Link State Advertisement.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex.description: The identifier of the link from which the LSA was received.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbIfInstId.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbIfInstId
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbIfInstId.description: The identifier of the interface instance from which the LSA was received.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbType.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbType
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format. Link-Scope LSAs unrecognized by the router are also stored in this database.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbLsid.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbLsid
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbAge.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbAge
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown.description: Indicates whether the LSA type is recognized by this Router.

jnxOspfv3HostTable.name: jnxOspfv3HostTable
jnxOspfv3HostTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.6 Host route parameters
jnxOspfv3HostTable.description: The list of Hosts, and their metrics, that the router will advertise as host routes. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as a part of RFC 5643.

jnxOspfv3HostEntry.name: jnxOspfv3HostEntry
jnxOspfv3HostEntry.description: A metric to be advertised when a given host is reachable.

jnxOspfv3HostAddressType.name: jnxOspfv3HostAddressType
jnxOspfv3HostAddressType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.6 Host route parameters
jnxOspfv3HostAddressType.description: The address type of ospfv3HostAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

jnxOspfv3HostAddress.name: jnxOspfv3HostAddress
jnxOspfv3HostAddress.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.6 Host route parameters
jnxOspfv3HostAddress.description: The IPv6 Address of the Host. Must be a Global address.

jnxOspfv3HostMetric.name: jnxOspfv3HostMetric
jnxOspfv3HostMetric.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.6 Host route parameters

jnxOspfv3HostStatus.name: jnxOspfv3HostStatus
jnxOspfv3HostStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

jnxOspfv3HostAreaID.name: jnxOspfv3HostAreaID
jnxOspfv3HostAreaID.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
jnxOspfv3HostAreaID.description: The Area the Host Entry is to be found within. By default, the area that a subsuming OSPFv3 interface is in, or Area 0

jnxOspfv3IfTable.name: jnxOspfv3IfTable
jnxOspfv3IfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3 Router interface parameters
jnxOspfv3IfTable.description: The OSPFv3 Interface Table describes the interfaces from the viewpoint of OSPFv3. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as a part of RFC 5643.

jnxOspfv3IfEntry.name: jnxOspfv3IfEntry
jnxOspfv3IfEntry.description: The OSPFv3 Interface Entry describes one interface from the viewpoint of OSPFv3.

jnxOspfv3IfIndex.name: jnxOspfv3IfIndex
jnxOspfv3IfIndex.description: The interface index of this OSPFv3 interface. It corresponds to the interface index of the IPv6 interface on which OSPFv3 is configured.

jnxOspfv3IfInstId.name: jnxOspfv3IfInstId
jnxOspfv3IfInstId.description: Enables multiple interface instances of OSPFv3 to be run over a single link. Each protocol instance would be assigned a separate ID. This ID has local link significance only.

jnxOspfv3IfAreaId.name: jnxOspfv3IfAreaId
jnxOspfv3IfAreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the area to which the interface connects. Area ID 0 is used for the OSPFv3 backbone.

jnxOspfv3IfAdminStat.name: jnxOspfv3IfAdminStat
jnxOspfv3IfAdminStat.description: The OSPFv3 interface's administrative status. The value formed on the interface, and the interface will be advertised as an internal route to some area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the interface is external to OSPFv3.

jnxOspfv3IfRtrPriority.name: jnxOspfv3IfRtrPriority
jnxOspfv3IfRtrPriority.description: The priority of this interface. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the router is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network. In the event of a tie in this value, routers will use their Router ID as a tie breaker.

jnxOspfv3IfTransitDelay.name: jnxOspfv3IfTransitDelay
jnxOspfv3IfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link state update packet over this interface.

jnxOspfv3IfRetransInterval.name: jnxOspfv3IfRetransInterval
jnxOspfv3IfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link state request packets.

jnxOspfv3IfHelloInterval.name: jnxOspfv3IfHelloInterval
jnxOspfv3IfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

jnxOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval.name: jnxOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval
jnxOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before its neighbors declare the router down on the interface. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

jnxOspfv3IfPollInterval.name: jnxOspfv3IfPollInterval
jnxOspfv3IfPollInterval.description: The larger time interval, in seconds, between the Hello packets sent to an inactive non-broadcast multi-access neighbor.

jnxOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter.name: jnxOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter
jnxOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter.description: The Router ID of the Designated Router.

jnxOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter.name: jnxOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter
jnxOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter.description: The Router ID of the Backup Designated Router.

jnxOspfv3IfEvents.name: jnxOspfv3IfEvents
jnxOspfv3IfEvents.description: The number of times this OSPF interface has changed its state, or an error has occurred.

jnxOspfv3IfStatus.name: jnxOspfv3IfStatus
jnxOspfv3IfStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

jnxOspfv3IfMulticastForwarding.name: jnxOspfv3IfMulticastForwarding
jnxOspfv3IfMulticastForwarding.description: The way multicasts should forwarded on this interface; not forwarded, forwarded as data link multicasts, or forwarded as data link unicasts. Data link multicasting is not meaningful on point to point and NBMA interfaces, and setting ospfv3MulticastForwarding to 0 effectively disables all multicast forwarding.

jnxOspfv3IfDemand.name: jnxOspfv3IfDemand
jnxOspfv3IfDemand.description: Indicates whether Demand OSPFv3 procedures (hello suppression to FULL neighbors and setting the DoNotAge flag on propagated LSAs) should be performed on this interface.

jnxOspfv3IfMetricValue.name: jnxOspfv3IfMetricValue
jnxOspfv3IfMetricValue.description: The metric assigned to this interface. The default value of the Metric is Reference Bandwidth / ifSpeed. The value of the reference bandwidth is configured by the ospfv3ReferenceBandwidth object.

jnxOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount.name: jnxOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount
jnxOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Link-Scope link state advertisements in this link's link state database.

jnxOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum.name: jnxOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum
jnxOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Link-Scope link state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this link's link state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link state database of two routers.

jnxOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbe.name: jnxOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbe
jnxOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbe.description: Indicates whether or not neighbor probing is enabled to determine whether or not the neighbor is inactive. Neighbor probing is disabled by default.

jnxOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeRetxLimit.name: jnxOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeRetxLimit
jnxOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeRetxLimit.description: The number of consecutive LSA retransmissions before the neighbor is deemed inactive and the neighbor adjacency is brought down.

jnxOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeInterval.name: jnxOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeInterval
jnxOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeInterval.description: Defines how often the neighbor will be probed.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfTable.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfTable
jnxOspfv3VirtIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.4 Virtual link parameters
jnxOspfv3VirtIfTable.description: Information about this router's virtual interfaces. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as a part of RFC 5643.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfEntry.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfEntry
jnxOspfv3VirtIfEntry.description: Information about a single Virtual Interface.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfAreaId.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfAreaId
jnxOspfv3VirtIfAreaId.description: The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not Area 0

jnxOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor
jnxOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfIndex.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfIndex
jnxOspfv3VirtIfIndex.description: The local interface index assigned to this OSPFv3 virtual interface. It is advertised in Hello's sent over the virtal link and in the router's router-LSAs.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfInstId.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfInstId
jnxOspfv3VirtIfInstId.description: Specifies the interface instance ID to be used for the virtual interface. This ID has local link significance only.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay
jnxOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link state update packet over this interface.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval
jnxOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round-trip time.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval
jnxOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval
jnxOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before its neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfState.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfState
jnxOspfv3VirtIfState.description: ospf virtual interface states. The same encoding as the ospfV3IfTable is used.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfEvents.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfEvents
jnxOspfv3VirtIfEvents.description: The number of state changes or error events on this Virtual Link

jnxOspfv3VirtIfStatus.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfStatus
jnxOspfv3VirtIfStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount
jnxOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Link-Scope link state advertisements in this virtual link's link state database.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum
jnxOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Link-Scope link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this virtual link's link-state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link state database of two routers.

jnxOspfv3NbrTable.name: jnxOspfv3NbrTable
jnxOspfv3NbrTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as a part of RFC 5643.
jnxOspfv3NbrTable.description: A table of non-virtual neighbor information.

jnxOspfv3NbrEntry.name: jnxOspfv3NbrEntry
jnxOspfv3NbrEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
jnxOspfv3NbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single neighbor.

jnxOspfv3NbrIfIndex.name: jnxOspfv3NbrIfIndex
jnxOspfv3NbrIfIndex.description: The local link ID of the link over which the neighbor can be reached.

jnxOspfv3NbrIfInstId.name: jnxOspfv3NbrIfInstId
jnxOspfv3NbrIfInstId.description: Interface instance over which the neighbor can be reached. This ID has local link significance only.

jnxOspfv3NbrRtrId.name: jnxOspfv3NbrRtrId
jnxOspfv3NbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

jnxOspfv3NbrAddressType.name: jnxOspfv3NbrAddressType
jnxOspfv3NbrAddressType.description: The address type of ospfv3NbrAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

jnxOspfv3NbrAddress.name: jnxOspfv3NbrAddress
jnxOspfv3NbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address of the neighbor associated with the local link.

jnxOspfv3NbrOptions.name: jnxOspfv3NbrOptions
jnxOspfv3NbrOptions.reference: OSPF Version 3, Appendix A.2 the Options field
jnxOspfv3NbrOptions.description: A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field.

jnxOspfv3NbrPriority.name: jnxOspfv3NbrPriority
jnxOspfv3NbrPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network.

jnxOspfv3NbrState.name: jnxOspfv3NbrState
jnxOspfv3NbrState.description: The State of the relationship with this Neighbor.

jnxOspfv3NbrEvents.name: jnxOspfv3NbrEvents
jnxOspfv3NbrEvents.description: The number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state, or an error has occurred.

jnxOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen.name: jnxOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen
jnxOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

jnxOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed.name: jnxOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed
jnxOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor

jnxOspfv3NbrIfId.name: jnxOspfv3NbrIfId
jnxOspfv3NbrIfId.description: The interface ID that the neighbor advertises in its Hello Packets on this link, that is, the neighbor's local interface index.

jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus.name: jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus
jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a Graceful restart helper for the neighbor.

jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge.name: jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge
jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF Graceful restart interval, if the router is acting as a restart helper for the neighbor.

jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitRc.name: jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitRc
jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitRc.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a Graceful restart helper for the neighbor. none:............no restart has yet been attempted. inProgress:......a restart attempt is currentlyly underway. completed:.......the last restart completed successfully. timedOut:........the last restart timed out. topologyChanged:.the last restart was aborted due to a topology change.

jnxOspfv3CfgNbrTable.name: jnxOspfv3CfgNbrTable
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrTable.description: A table of configured, non-virtual neighbor information. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as a part of RFC 5643.

jnxOspfv3CfgNbrEntry.name: jnxOspfv3CfgNbrEntry
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single configured neighbor or neighbor discovered by lower-level protocols such as Inverse Neighbor Discovery.

jnxOspfv3CfgNbrIfIndex.name: jnxOspfv3CfgNbrIfIndex
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrIfIndex.description: The local link ID of the link over which the neighbor can be reached.

jnxOspfv3CfgNbrIfInstId.name: jnxOspfv3CfgNbrIfInstId
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrIfInstId.description: Interface instance over which the neighbor can be reached. This ID has local link significance only.

jnxOspfv3CfgNbrAddressType.name: jnxOspfv3CfgNbrAddressType
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrAddressType.description: The address type of ospfv3NbrAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

jnxOspfv3CfgNbrAddress.name: jnxOspfv3CfgNbrAddress
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address of the neighbor associated with the local link.

jnxOspfv3CfgNbrPriority.name: jnxOspfv3CfgNbrPriority
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network.

jnxOspfv3CfgNbrStatus.name: jnxOspfv3CfgNbrStatus
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrTable.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrTable
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrTable.description: A table of virtual neighbor information. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as a part of RFC 5643.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex.description: The local interface ID for the virtual link over which the neighbor can be reached.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrIfInstId.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrIfInstId
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrIfInstId.description: The interface instance for the virtual link over which the neighbor can be reached.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType.description: The address type of ospfv3VirtNbrAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrAddress.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrAddress
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address advertised by this Virtual Neighbor. It must be a Global scope address.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrOptions
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.reference: OSPF Version 3, Appendix A.2 the Options field
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.description: A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrState.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrState
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrState.description: The state of the Virtual Neighbor Relationship.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrEvents.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrEvents
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrEvents.description: The number of times this virtual link has changed its state, or an error has occurred.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrIfId.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrIfId
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrIfId.description: The interface ID that the neighbor advertises in its Hello Packets on this virtual link, that is, the neighbor's local interface ID.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a Graceful restart helper for the neighbor.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF Graceful restart interval, if the router is acting as a restart helper for the neighbor.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitRc.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitRc
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitRc.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a Graceful restart helper for the neighbor. none:............no restart has yet been attempted. inProgress:......a restart attempt is currently underway. completed:.......the last restart completed successfully. timedOut:........the last restart timed out. topologyChanged:.the last restart was aborted due to a topology change.

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateTable.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateTable
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateTable.description: A range of IPv6 prefixes specified by a prefix/prefix length pair. Note that if ranges are configured such that one range subsumes another range the most specific match is the preferred one. Marking this table and its objects deprecated as it is now implemented as part of RFC 5643.

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.description: A range of IPv6 prefixes specified by a prefix/prefix length pair. Note that if ranges are configured such that one range subsumes another range the most specific match is the preferred one.

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID.description: The Area the Address Aggregate is to be found within.

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.1 The Link State Advertisement header
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.description: The type of the Address Aggregate. This field specifies the Area Lsdb type that this Address Aggregate applies to.

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixType.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixType
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixType.description: The prefix type of ospfv3AreaAggregatePrefix. Only IPv6 addresses are expected.

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix (in bits). A prefix can not be shorter than 3 bits.

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateStatus.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateStatus
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect.description: Prefixes subsumed by ranges either trigger the advertisement of the indicated aggregate (advertiseMatching), or result in the prefix not being advertised at all outside the area.

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateRouteTag.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateRouteTag
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateRouteTag.description: This tag is advertised only in the summarized As-External LSA when summarizing from NSSA-LSA's to AS-External-LSA's.

jnxOspfv3ConfigErrorType.name: jnxOspfv3ConfigErrorType
jnxOspfv3ConfigErrorType.description: Potential types of configuration conflicts. Used by the ospfv3ConfigError and ospfv3ConfigVirtError notifications. When the last value of a notification using this object is needed, but no notifications of that type have been sent, this value pertaining to this object should be returned as noError

jnxOspfv3PacketType.name: jnxOspfv3PacketType
jnxOspfv3PacketType.description: OSPFv3 packet types. When the last value of a notification using this object is needed, but no notifications of that type have been sent, the value pertaining to this object should be returned as nullPacket

jnxOspfv3PacketSrc.name: jnxOspfv3PacketSrc
jnxOspfv3PacketSrc.description: The IPv6 address of an inbound packet that cannot be identified by a neighbor instance. When the last value of a notification using this object is needed, but no notifications of that type have been sent, the value pertaining to this object should be returned as 0 Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfStateChange.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfStateChange
jnxOspfv3VirtIfStateChange.description: An ospfv3VirtIfStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of an OSPFv3 virtual interface. This notification should be generated when the interface state regresses (e.g., goes from Point-to-Point to Down) or progresses to a terminal state (i.e., Point-to-Point).

jnxOspfv3NbrStateChange.name: jnxOspfv3NbrStateChange
jnxOspfv3NbrStateChange.description: An ospfv3NbrStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of a non-virtual OSPFv3 neighbor. This notification should be generated when the neighbor state regresses (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full to 1-Way or Down) or progresses to a terminal state (e.g., 2-Way or Full). When an neighbor transitions from or to Full on non-broadcast multi-access and broadcast networks, the notification should be generated by the designated router. A designated router transitioning to Down will be noted by ospfIfStateChange.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrStateChange.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrStateChange
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrStateChange.description: An ospfv3VirtNbrStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of an OSPFv3 virtual neighbor. This notification should be generated when the neighbor state regresses (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full to 1-Way or Down) or progresses to a terminal state (e.g., Full).

jnxOspfv3IfConfigError.name: jnxOspfv3IfConfigError
jnxOspfv3IfConfigError.description: An ospfv3IfConfigError notification signifies that a packet has been received on a non-virtual interface from a router whose configuration parameters conflict with this router's configuration parameters. Note that the event optionMismatch should cause a notification only if it prevents an adjacency from forming.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfConfigError.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfConfigError
jnxOspfv3VirtIfConfigError.description: An ospfv3VirtIfConfigError notification signifies that a packet has been received on a virtual interface from a router whose configuration parameters conflict with this router's configuration parameters. Note that the event optionMismatch should cause a notification only if it prevents an adjacency from forming.

jnxOspfv3IfRxBadPacket.name: jnxOspfv3IfRxBadPacket
jnxOspfv3IfRxBadPacket.description: An ospfv3IfRxBadPacket notification signifies that an ospfv3 packet that cannot be parsed has been received on a non-virtual interface.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket
jnxOspfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket.description: An ospfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket notification signifies that an OSPFv3 packet that cannot be parsed has been received on a virtual interface.

jnxOspfv3LsdbOverflow.name: jnxOspfv3LsdbOverflow
jnxOspfv3LsdbOverflow.description: An ospfv3LsdbOverflow notification signifies that the number of LSAs in the router's link-state database has exceeded ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.

jnxOspfv3LsdbApproachingOverflow.name: jnxOspfv3LsdbApproachingOverflow
jnxOspfv3LsdbApproachingOverflow.description: An ospfv3LsdbApproachingOverflow notification signifies that the number of LSAs in the router's link-state database has exceeded ninety percent of ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.

jnxOspfv3IfStateChange.name: jnxOspfv3IfStateChange
jnxOspfv3IfStateChange.description: An ospfv3IfStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of a non-virtual OSPFv3 interface. This notification should be generated when the interface state regresses (e.g., goes from Dr to Down) or progresses to a terminal state (i.e., Point-to-Point, DR Other, Dr, or Backup).

jnxOspfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange.name: jnxOspfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange
jnxOspfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange.description: An ospfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange notification indicates that there has been a change in the router's ability to translate OSPFv3 NSSA LSAs into OSPFv3 External LSAs. This notification should be generated when the Translator Status transitions from or to any defined status on a per area basis.

jnxOspfv3RestartStatusChange.name: jnxOspfv3RestartStatusChange
jnxOspfv3RestartStatusChange.description: An ospfv3RestartStatusChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the graceful restart state for the router. This notification should be generated when the router restart status changes.

jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange.name: jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange
jnxOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange.description: An ospfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the graceful restart helper state for the neighbor. This notification should be generated when the neighbor restart helper status transitions for a neighbor.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChang.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChange
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChang.description: An ospfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the graceful restart helper state for the virtual neighbor. This notification should be generated when the virtual neighbor restart helper status transitions for a virtual neighbor.

jnxOspfv3BasicGroup.name: jnxOspfv3BasicGroup
jnxOspfv3BasicGroup.description: These objects are used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 global parameters.

jnxOspfv3AreaGroup.name: jnxOspfv3AreaGroup
jnxOspfv3AreaGroup.description: These objects are used for ospfv3 systems supporting areas.

jnxOspfv3AsLsdbGroup.name: jnxOspfv3AsLsdbGroup
jnxOspfv3AsLsdbGroup.description: These objects are used for ospfv3 systems that display their AS-scope link state database.

jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbGroup.name: jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbGroup
jnxOspfv3AreaLsdbGroup.description: These objects are used for OSPFv3 systems that display their Area-scope link state database.

jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbGroup.name: jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbGroup
jnxOspfv3LinkLsdbGroup.description: These objects are used for OSPFv3 systems that display their Link-scope link state database.

jnxOspfv3HostGroup.name: jnxOspfv3HostGroup
jnxOspfv3HostGroup.description: These objects are used for OSPFv3 systems that support attached hosts.

jnxOspfv3IfGroup.name: jnxOspfv3IfGroup
jnxOspfv3IfGroup.description: These interface objects used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 interfaces.

jnxOspfv3VirtIfGroup.name: jnxOspfv3VirtIfGroup
jnxOspfv3VirtIfGroup.description: These virtual interface objects are used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 virtual interfaces.

jnxOspfv3NbrGroup.name: jnxOspfv3NbrGroup
jnxOspfv3NbrGroup.description: These neighbor objects are used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 neighbors.

jnxOspfv3CfgNbrGroup.name: jnxOspfv3CfgNbrGroup
jnxOspfv3CfgNbrGroup.description: These configured neighbor objects are used for managing/monitoring ospfv3 configured neighbors.

jnxOspfv3VirtNbrGroup.name: jnxOspfv3VirtNbrGroup
jnxOspfv3VirtNbrGroup.description: These virtual neighbor objects are used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 virtual neighbors.

jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateGroup.name: jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateGroup
jnxOspfv3AreaAggregateGroup.description: These area aggregate objects used required for aggregating OSPFv3 prefixes for summarization across areas.

jnxOspfv3NotificationObjectGroup.name: jnxOspfv3NotificationObjectGroup
jnxOspfv3NotificationObjectGroup.description: These objects are used to record notification parameters

jnxOspfv3NotificationGroup.name: jnxOspfv3NotificationGroup
jnxOspfv3NotificationGroup.description: This group is used for OSPFv3 notifications
